headline: Wall Street Lunch: Retail Sales Stall In December As Middle And Lower-Income Consumers Hit Pause
summary: Retail sales were flat in December, missing expectations for a 0.4% increase and slowing from 0.6% growth in November. Sales were up 2.4% from a year ago.
